### 4. CSS Classes to Add to `CanvasEditor.module.css`

```css
/* Minimap container - bottom-left of stageShell */
.minimapContainer {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0.8rem;
    bottom: 0.7rem;
    z-index: 2;
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 52, 41, 0.28);
    background: rgba(242, 236, 225, 0.72);   /* matches light paper tone */
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    box-shadow:
        0 4px 14px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.14),
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    cursor: crosshair;
    overflow: hidden;
    opacity: 0.88;
    transition: opacity 180ms ease;
}

.minimapContainer:hover {
    opacity: 1;
}

.minimapDark {
    border-color: rgba(198, 209, 220, 0.22);
    background: rgba(17, 22, 28, 0.76);
    box-shadow:
        0 4px 14px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.36),
        inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
}

/* The draggable viewport rectangle */
.minimapViewport {
    position: absolute;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1.5px solid rgba(90, 211, 159, 0.85);
    background: rgba(90, 211, 159, 0.15);
    cursor: grab;
    /* No transition here - must track mouse exactly without lag */
}

.minimapViewport:active {
    cursor: grabbing;
    background: rgba(90, 211, 159, 0.25);
    border-color: #5ad39f;
}
```

**Key CSS decisions:**

- `left: 0.8rem; bottom: 0.7rem` mirrors the `stageHud` positioning on the opposite corner. No overlap.
- `z-index: 2` matches `stageHud` so both sit above the canvas but below `PieMenu` (z-index: 50 in its overlay).
- `overflow: hidden` on the container clips any edge-case rect overflow.
- No `transition` on `.minimapViewport` position - inline `style` updates from React are synchronous with mouse events; transitions would cause a visible lag.
- The green `#5ad39f` matches the existing selection/active color used throughout the editor (`toolButtonActive`, `snippetInput:focus`, etc.).

